Key Match Events: Philadelphia Phillies rallied to shock the Atlanta Braves in Thursday's series opener.
Matt Olson hit his second home run of the game off Cristopher Sanchez.
Brandon Marsh hit a three-run homer to tie the game.
Nick Castellanos hit a go-ahead two-run homer off Grant Holmes.
Matt Strahm and Jeff Hoffman held the Braves scoreless over the final two innings to preserve the 5-4 victory.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The win improved Philadelphia's record to 79-55, six games ahead of second-place Atlanta in the NL East standings.
The two teams will square off again on Friday in a potential pitching duel between All-Stars Reynaldo Lopez and Ranger Suarez.
